spark.sql("set spark.sql.shuffle.partitions=3"); //improve performance by reducing the default number of partitions
val batchDf = spark
        .read  // readStream for structured streaming ;)
        .format("csv") 
        .option("header", "true") //reading the headers
        .option("delimiter",";") //set delimiter 
        .option("mode", "DROPMALFORMED")
        .csv("/usr/zeppelin/data/bank/bank-full.csv")
        
batchDf.isStreaming
batchDf.show(5)
batchDf.registerTempTable("bank")

paragraphs.title: Streaming Query example
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.sql.streaming._
import scala.concurrent.duration._
    val query=spark
      .readStream
      .format("kafka")
      .option("kafka.bootstrap.servers", "192.168.99.100:9092")
      .option("subscribe", "alarms,data")
      .option("group.id", "structured-Streaming-demo")
      .option("failOnDataLoss", true) 
      .load()
      .select(col("topic"), from_json(col("value").cast("string"),mySchema).alias("parsed_value")) //select kafka_topic, parse incoming data
      .select("topic","parsed_value.*") //explode incominf data
      .writeStream
      .format("memory") //with memory output we can use sparkSQL to test our streaming query
      .queryName("test")
      .trigger(Trigger.ProcessingTime(10.seconds)) //if we do not trigger will start another 'batch' as soon as the job finishes
      .start()

paragraphs.title: Streaming Query data
paragraphs.text:
%sql
select * from test

paragraphs.title: Watermarked aggregation
paragraphs.text:
%spark
import org.apache.spark.sql.streaming._
import scala.concurrent.duration._
    val query=spark
      .readStream
      .format("kafka")
      .option("kafka.bootstrap.servers", "192.168.99.100:9092")
      .option("subscribe", "alarms,data")
      .option("group.id", "structured-Streaming-demo")
      .option("failOnDataLoss", true) 
      .load()
      .select(col("topic"), from_json(col("value").cast("string"),mySchema).alias("parsed_value"))
      .select("parsed_value.*")
      .withWatermark("timestamp", "1 minutes")
      .dropDuplicates("machine","timestamp")
      .groupBy("machine","timestamp")
      .avg("humidity").as("AVG Humidity")
      .writeStream
      .format("memory")
      .queryName("test")
       .outputMode(OutputMode.Complete)
      .trigger(Trigger.ProcessingTime(10.seconds)) //if we do not trigger will start another 'batch' as soon as the job finishes
      .start()

%sql 
select * from test

paragraphs.title: Non Watermarked vs Watermarked Windowed Count Query
paragraphs.text:
%spark
import org.apache.spark.sql.streaming._
import scala.concurrent.duration._
    val query=spark
      .readStream
      .format("kafka")
      .option("kafka.bootstrap.servers", "192.168.99.100:9092")
      .option("subscribe", "alarms,data")
      .option("group.id", "structured-Streaming-demo")
      .option("failOnDataLoss", true) 
      .load()
      .select(col("topic"), from_json(col("value").cast("string"),mySchema).alias("parsed_value"))
      .select("parsed_value.*")
      .groupBy($"machine", window($"timestamp", "2 minutes"))
      .count()
      .writeStream
      .format("memory")
      .queryName("count")
       .outputMode(OutputMode.Complete)
      .trigger(Trigger.ProcessingTime(10.seconds)) //if we do not trigger will start another 'batch' as soon as the job finishes
